The President has issued an Executive Order aimed at addressing the threat of malicious cyber activity. This Order grants the Secretary of the Treasury the authority to impose sanctions on individuals or entities engaged in cyber activities that pose a significant threat to national security, foreign policy, or the economic health of the United States. The activities targeted by the Order include harming critical infrastructure, stealing funds or trade secrets for economic advantage, disrupting computer networks, and providing support for these activities. The President intends to use various tools, such as diplomatic engagement and law enforcement, to counter cyber threats. This Order is part of a comprehensive strategy to confront cyber threats and adds a new authority to combat the most serious malicious cyber activity.